<sect3 id="sect_definingIntegerLongFields" label="2">
    <title id="title_definingIntegerLongFields">Defining integer and long fields</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>Table fields of the type <guimenuitem>INTEGER</guimenuitem> or
                            <guimenuitem>LONG</guimenuitem> are both used to save whole numbers.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Type specific field details</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>
                            <figure id="fig_integerFieldDetails">
                                <title> Integer field details</title>
                                <screenshot>
                                    <mediaobject>
                                        <imageobject>
                                            <imagedata
                                                fileref="./Screenshots/IntegerFieldDetails.jpg"
                                                format="JPEG" scalefit="1" width="237" depth="93"/>
                                        </imageobject>
                                    </mediaobject>
                                </screenshot>
                            </figure>
                        </para>
                        <para>For integer and long fields it is necessary to specify the following
                            field details:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>a <guilabel>Default value</guilabel> can be declared;</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>by setting the <guilabel>Min value</guilabel> and
                                        <guilabel>Max value</guilabel> you can create ranges and</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>the <guilabel>Autoincrement</guilabel> check box enables the
                                    consecutive numbering e.g. for primary keys.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Boolean fields</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>Boolean like table fields can be created by setting the
                                <guilabel>Min value</guilabel> to "0" and the <guilabel>Max value</guilabel>
                            to "1" .</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect3>
